  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD pipeline is implemented as a multi-stage software workflow comprising a commercial Navier-Stokes solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2), a custom Python-based hemolysis post-processor applying the Giersiepen power-law model, and a batch orchestration layer coordinating parallel parametric sweeps across the 5 flow-speed operating points. All validation runs completed nominally; no solver divergence events were logged during the assessment campaign.",
