      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-01-piv-velocity-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field benchmark — nominal completion",
      "description": "CFD-predicted velocity magnitudes compared against FDA PIV experimental data for the generic centrifugal blood pump at 2.5 L/min and 3500 RPM. All 5 cross-sectional planes assessed. Run completed without interruption; residuals converged to 1e-5 within 800 iterations. Agreement within 8% RMS across measurement planes, satisfying the acceptance threshold of 15% RMS for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-02-wall-shear-stress-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress distribution comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Predicted wall shear stress distributions compared against published LDV measurements from the Morrison et al. (2020) dataset. The hemolysis post-processor Python script executed without exception across all 5 operating points. Peak WSS values agreed within 12% of experimental measurements. A single operating point at 6 L/min / 4500 RPM required residual relaxation from 0.7 to 0.5 to achieve convergence, but this was treated as a routine tuning step and the run is reported as nominally complete."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-03-hemolysis-index-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against predicate — nominal completion",
      "description": "Computed RH values for all 5 flow-speed combinations compared against predicate device hemolysis index measured in vitro. All 5 RH values satisfied the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Post-processing pipeline completed nominally across all parametric sweep cases. No NaN or Inf values were detected in the final output tables; intermediate scalar transport fields were not audited for floating-point exceptions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-04-mesh-independence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1M, 5.4M, 11.2M cells) evaluated for the nominal operating point (4 L/min, 3500 RPM). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Celik et al. (2008). GCI for hemolysis scalar < 3.5%, satisfying the MRL 2 threshold of 5%. All three mesh runs completed without solver crash or iteration limit breach."
    }
