      "rationale": "PIV and LDV experimental conditions documented in Morrison et al. (2020) with fluid temperature 37±0.5°C, hematocrit 35±2%, flow rates ±0.05 L/min, and rotational speed ±10 RPM. CFD boundary conditions set to match experimental nominal values. Correspondence between experimental and simulation conditions confirmed for all 5 operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (RMS error, peak error) computed for velocity fields and hemolysis index; agreement within 15% RMS for velocity and 20% for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field RMS error 8% across all PIV comparison planes. Hemolysis index prediction within 18% of in vitro measurements for all 5 operating points, satisfying the 20% acceptance criterion. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 for all cases, confirming the primary acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, relative hemolysis index RH) are directly linked to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and derived relative hemolysis index (RH), which are the FDA-recognized metrics for hemolysis assessment in blood-contacting devices. These QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical risk of hemolysis in CPB patients and to the regulatory submission criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
