      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same pump geometry class, operating range, and fluid properties as the COU; validation domain overlaps with COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the reference geometry for the COU device class. Operating conditions span 2.5–6 L/min and 3000–4500 RPM, encompassing the COU operating envelope. Blood analog fluid properties match COU conditions. The validation dataset is therefore directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
